name: Westchester County Health Department
tweet: The FDA and CDC have approved the use of heterologous or “mix and match” booster doses for COVID-19 vaccines. People who are eligible can get a booster shot with any available COVID-19 vaccine, regardless of whether they initially received the J&J, Moderna, or Pfizer vaccine.  https://t.co/fVEN3Kd3tx

name: Westchester County Health Department
tweet: With booster doses rolling out, many people have questions about the effectiveness of the COVID-19 vaccines. The vaccines remain safe & highly protective against severe COVID. If you have questions about why or when you might need a booster—learn more:  https://t.co/7wxgAusQFV  https://t.co/NUMXEL4a4m

name: Westchester County Health Department
tweet: Millions of Americans are now eligible to get a COVID-19 booster dose! The CDC has approved Pfizer, Moderna, and J&J booster shots for certain groups. Eligible individuals may choose which vaccine they receive as a booster dose.  https://t.co/EhbdGkzDRO

name: Westchester County Health Department
tweet: The decision to protect your sexual health is in your hands, literally. PrEP is an affordable and effective pill you can take once daily or on-demand to keep you from getting HIV. Learn more:  https://t.co/yictbTj26C  #PrEPAwareWeek2021  https://t.co/9xRwmCr9Fu
